Description: Two joining sherds of rim and upper body of small pottery closed vessels with horizontal handles, one partly preserved. Model of a Cypriot basket-handled amphora made of local Nile silt fabric (?)
Curator's comments: The fabric is very fine for local Nile silt, though the small models of transport amphorae found at Naukratis look very similar.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IB.064)
